      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-sqa",
        "description": "Commercial FEA software (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R1) used under vendor-maintained QMS; FDA OSEL in-house solver subject to internal SOP-FEA-001 version control and regression test suite. Minimum required: documented version control and regression testing (Gradation 2). Achieved: full regression suite with documented pass records and independent code review (Gradation 3)."
      },
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical operated under ISO 9001-certified vendor QMS with documented release validation. FDA OSEL solver maintained under SOP-FEA-001 with Git-based version control, automated regression tests (47 benchmark cases, 100% pass), and peer code review. DePuy Synthes solver covered by corporate QMS. All three ensemble members satisfy Gradation 3 SQA requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-ncv",
        "description": "Code verification via comparison to analytical solutions for beam bending and contact mechanics problems. Required: patch test and at least one analytical benchmark (Gradation 2). Achieved: patch test, Hertzian contact benchmark, and cantilever beam benchmark with documented convergence rates (Gradation 3)."
      },
      "rationale": "All three FEA solvers verified against: (1) standard patch test for element completeness; (2) Hertzian contact pressure benchmark (max error <0.5%); (3) Euler-Bernoulli cantilever beam deflection benchmark (max error <0.3%). Convergence rates consistent with theoretical order. Results documented in Nagaraja et al. Supplementary Material S1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-disc-error",
        "description": "Mesh convergence study with Richardson extrapolation or equivalent. Required: at least two mesh densities with documented QoI sensitivity (Gradation 2). Achieved: three mesh densities with Richardson extrapolation and GCI calculation (Gradation 3)."
      },
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed on non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw construct using three mesh densities (coarse: 28k elements, medium: 112k elements, fine: 448k elements). Richardson extrapolation applied to stiffness and yield force QoIs. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for fine mesh: 0.8% for stiffness, 1.1% for yield force — both below 2% threshold. Fine mesh selected for all production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-solver-error",
        "description": "Iterative solver convergence monitored and documented. Required: solver convergence criteria documented (Gradation 1). Achieved: convergence criteria documented with residual history plots and energy balance check (Gradation 2)."
      },
      "rationale": "Nonlinear quasi-static analyses used Newton-Raphson iteration with force residual tolerance 1e-4 and displacement residual tolerance 1e-5. Energy balance verified at each load step (energy error <0.01%). Residual histories archived for all 33 production runs (11 specimens × 3 solvers). No convergence failures observed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-use-error",
        "description": "Documented analysis plan reviewed by independent analyst prior to execution. Required: documented analysis plan with independent review (Gradation 2). Achieved: pre-registered analysis plan reviewed and signed off by two independent analysts (Gradation 2)."
      },
      "rationale": "Analysis plan pre-registered as OSEL-AP-2021-047 prior to any simulation runs. Plan documented boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, load application, and QoI extraction procedures. Independent review performed by two analysts not involved in model development (sign-off dates 2021-03-12 and 2021-03-15). Post-hoc deviations: none."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-model-form",
        "description": "Model form justified by physics and prior literature. Required: documented justification of constitutive model and contact formulation with reference to prior validation evidence (Gradation 3). Achieved: bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V justified by tensile coupon data and prior literature; penalty contact with friction coefficient justified by tribological data (Gradation 3)."
      },
      "rationale": "Continuum FEA with bilinear isotropic hardening (E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, E_t=2.3 GPa) for Ti-6Al-4V screw and rod; UHMWPE vertebral body surrogate modeled as linear elastic (E=1.1 GPa). Constitutive parameters derived from material coupon testing (n=5 per batch). Augmented Lagrangian contact with μ=0.2 (Ti-Ti interface) and μ=0.15 (Ti-UHMWPE) consistent with published tribological data. Model form consistent with prior FDA/ASTM F1717 FEA literature."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-model-inputs",
        "description": "Material properties and geometric inputs derived from direct measurement of test specimens. Required: specimen-specific geometry and batch-specific material properties with documented uncertainty (Gradation 3). Achieved: CMM-measured geometry for each of N=11 specimens; tensile coupon data from same material batch; dimensional uncertainty <0.05 mm (Gradation 3)."
      },
      "rationale": "Screw and rod geometry digitized via CMM (accuracy ±0.02 mm) for each of the 11 test specimens; specimen-specific FEA models built from CMM point clouds. Material properties (E, σ_y, E_t) measured from tensile coupons machined from same Ti-6Al-4V bar stock (n=5 coupons, CV<2%). UHMWPE block properties from supplier datasheet confirmed by compression testing (n=3). Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (n=1000) to produce combined uval per QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-test-samples",
        "description": "Test samples representative of production devices with documented traceability. Required: production-representative samples with documented lot traceability and dimensional inspection (Gradation 3). Achieved: N=11 production-equivalent non-cannulated 7.5 mm screws from two manufacturing lots, fully dimensionally inspected, with chain-of-custody documentation (Gradation 3)."
      },
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production-equivalent components (Lots A and B, n=6 and n=5 respectively). All screws and rods dimensionally inspected per DePuy Synthes IQC procedure QP-4421. Chain-of-custody documentation maintained from manufacturer to each test laboratory. No out-of-tolerance specimens identified. Inter-lot dimensional variability <1% for all critical dimensions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-test-conditions",
        "description": "Test conditions documented and matched to FEA boundary conditions. Required: multiple test conditions spanning clinically relevant range (Gradation 3). Achieved: single ASTM F1717 standard test condition (44 mm offset, 10 mm/min crosshead speed) with full documentation — insufficient to achieve Gradation 3 but Gradation 2 accepted given corroborating evidence from prior multi-condition studies in literature."
      },
      "rationale": "Testing performed under ASTM F1717-15 standard conditions only: 44 mm anterior offset, ambient temperature (23±2°C), 10 mm/min crosshead speed, 5 N preload. Single test condition limits factor to Gradation 2 (below required Gradation 3). Risk accepted per decision record DR-2021-047: the single condition represents the regulatory submission condition; prior literature (Brekelmans et al., 2019) demonstrates FEA model accuracy is not strongly condition-dependent for this construct type. Residual risk documented and accepted by credibility assessment team.",
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-dr-2021-047/factor/test-conditions"
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-input-equiv",
        "description": "FEA boundary conditions demonstrably equivalent to experimental test conditions. Required: documented mapping of all experimental boundary conditions to FEA inputs with quantified equivalency (Gradation 3). Achieved: all six experimental boundary condition parameters mapped to FEA inputs with measured equivalency within ±2% (Gradation 3)."
      },
      "rationale": "Systematic mapping of experimental-to-FEA boundary conditions: (1) 44 mm offset fixture geometry replicated in FEA to ±0.1 mm; (2) crosshead displacement applied as prescribed displacement BC; (3) load cell compliance measured and incorporated as spring element; (4) fixture pin friction measured (μ=0.12±0.02) and applied; (5) specimen alignment verified via optical measurement and replicated in FEA; (6) preload applied as initial step. All six parameters within ±2% equivalency threshold. Documented in Supplementary Material S2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-output-comparison",
        "description": "Quantitative comparison of FEA predictions to experimental measurements using validation metric that accounts for both model error and combined uncertainty. Required: quantitative metric with uncertainty (Gradation 3). Achieved: E/uval metric applied to all three QoIs across all 11 specimens with ensemble statistics; all E/uval < 1.96 (Gradation 4)."
      },
      "rationale": "ASME V&V 10.1 validation metric E/uval computed for each QoI: stiffness E/uval=0.87 (95% CI: 0.71–1.03), yield force E/uval=1.31 (95% CI: 1.12–1.50), force at 40 mm E/uval=1.54 (95% CI: 1.33–1.75). All three below threshold of 1.96. Percent differences: 4.2%, 6.8%, 7.9% — all below 10% threshold. Ensemble agreement across three independent solvers provides additional confidence. Full specimen-level comparison table in Supplementary Material S3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-qoi-relevance",
        "description": "QoIs directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory acceptance criteria. Required: documented traceability from QoIs to clinical endpoints and regulatory requirements (Gradation 3). Achieved: stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement directly linked to ASTM F1717 acceptance criteria and clinical failure mode analysis (Gradation 3)."
      },
      "rationale": "Three QoIs selected based on ASTM F1717 regulatory submission requirements and clinical failure mode analysis: (1) construct stiffness — surrogate for in vivo load sharing and fatigue life; (2) yield force — onset of permanent deformation, directly linked to intraoperative overload risk; (3) force at 40 mm displacement — regulatory submission criterion per ASTM F1717 Table 1. Traceability matrix linking each QoI to clinical failure mode documented in OSEL-TM-2021-047."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nagaraja-validation-relevance",
        "description": "Validation activities directly representative of COU geometry, loading, and material. Required: validation performed on same device geometry under same loading conditions as COU (Gradation 3). Achieved: validation performed on production-equivalent non-cannulated 7.5 mm screws under ASTM F1717 conditions identical to COU (Gradation 3)."
      },
      "rationale": "Validation activity is co-extensive with the COU: same device (non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw), same construct configuration (two screws, one rod, two UHMWPE vertebral body surrogates), same loading mode (compression-bending per ASTM F1717), same acceptance criteria (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96). No extrapolation from validation domain to COU domain required. The single gap — single test condition vs. multi-condition requirement — is documented under Test Conditions factor and accepted with rationale."
    }
